text: A few squawks here a few squawks there. All makes the world go round.
My parrot-mobile is leaking fluid on the monkeys on the branches below. They are throwing banana peels at me. Also. I'm out of seeds.
Why fly like an eagle when you could soar AND squawk like a parrot?
My girl just laid an egg. Suggested taking it to planned parrothood, but instead a villager took it and ate it this morning.
Darn doctors handwriting messed up my birth certificate. Spent the first three years of life wondering why im not orange and skinny.
Less majestic than the eagle; but more so than a parakeet. Classier than a seagull. Also classier than a parakeet.
